# SaaS Rules

## Purpose
Venture-scale SaaS: billing, quotas, onboarding, retention per `docs/BILLING_SPEC.md` and `docs/GROWTH_STRATEGY.md`.

## Requirements
- Enforce plan limits on create (properties, employees, AI minutes) — BR-T04.
- Trial 14 days; suspended org read-only mode BR-T02.
- Usage counters in `organization_usage` kept in sync via events or transactional increments.
- Onboarding empty states guide activation (5 properties, 2 employees).
- Feature availability gated by plan tier and feature flags.

## Restrictions
- No unlimited free tier bypassing billing checks.
- No hard-coded tenant exceptions in code — use feature flags or support tools with audit.

## Best Practices
- Cache plan limits Redis 5m; invalidate on subscription webhook.
- Grace period messaging in UI for past_due.
- Metrics hooks for activation funnel events.

## Anti-Patterns
- Checking billing in frontend only.
- Silent failure when quota exceeded — return 422 `QUOTA_EXCEEDED`.

## Examples

```typescript
await this.quotaService.assertCanCreateProperty(ctx.tenantId);
// throws QuotaExceededException with upgrade CTA payload
```
